 With the zone wide DT's, I think CT should now be a triggered spawn instead of always roaming.  Like once you clear the zone, or kill the 3 golems/draco, or something.  With this new CT in town and the upgrading of mobs, the zone will be VERY BAD with him DT'ing like a mad monkey.<br><br> <p>Lerwin the Mighty<BR>53rd lvl Vicar, Outcast of Tunare<BR>The Original High Elf of Rivervale<BR>Sorrow`s End<BR>Raving Lunatic by Heart</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umercurato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mercurato</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/mercurato/eye.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/27/01 2:59:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CT and stuff</span><hr size=1> With all these changes I hope they made upgrades to PoG.  As it is alot of people are just skipping their hate/fear armor.  Maybe even just limit PoG to 54+ or something.<br><br>Merc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulorrux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lorrux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/27/01 7:22:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question </span><hr size=1> I'm still a noob I guess cause I have yet to go to any of the planes. But wtf is up with a change like this, if it in fact goes live. Are they trying to turn POH/POF where only 55-60 players are the only ones who can hunt there. I mean I still hear of wipeouts so is there really a problem with the Planes being too easy is I guess the question I'm trying to pose. Evidently PoG may need some nerfing perhaps, but I grow tired of Verant thinking the way to a better game is by jacking us around by changing stuff midstream with little thought of the customer(especially when POH/POF has been in game for almost 2+ years). <br><br>Also if they do go live with these changes would it even be viable for a character just planes capable to even go there if the mobs are going to be super-red now? I'm just a bubble away from 46 and was planning to try to level to 47/48 before my first journey there so I can be of some use hopefully, but after reading this I wonder why bother. Or at least hurry up and level before they patch this into the game. Is the Risk going to be worth the reward?<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugemencracknazi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gemen Cracknazi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/01 12:35:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question </span><hr size=1> Hell, I'm 52 now, an' I think this is a load of shite. People try so hard to get past the level 45 hump just to be 'planar'. You all remember what that means, right? No longer are you restricted to the mundane &quot;old world&quot;. You can be part of a monter raid on another plane of reality, get thrown in with a bunch of mad powerful mobs, and actually use strategy in addition to overwhelming numbers to get the job done. It's an amazing experience to finally go to your first plane of Hate/Fear raid, and I'm not exactly looking forward to having to play another 4 months just to be high enough level to be of any use there. There are really very few zones of similar level that hold the same appeal as the planes do. As I've gone up in levels, all of this new content being thrown at the high-level players has impressed me far less than my first trip to the planes of Fear and Hate. Maybe I'm just expecting too much of the game nowadays.. Maybe I just think everyone should go through the same emotion I did when I could finally get into that elusive 'planar club'. All I can say is that if these changes go live, I genuinely feel sorry for those of you who haven't reached your forty sixth level yet. It kills me to see you all deprived of such an experience in order to further along some inane power struggle between a company and the players that keep one-upping them.<br><br>- The Man <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uungarraventhorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ungar Raventhorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/01 2:11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question </span><hr size=1> Nerfing planes is probably the only way to keep things balance. Keep in mind PoF / PoH were designed before Kunark and allowing level 50 plus players to farm the zone is just too easy. There is a huge difference in difficulty between bringing in 3 groups of level 50 characters equiped with the best gear Lower Guk can offer and 3 groups of level 54 characters with Kunark gear.<br><br>In the past Verant nerfed Vox and Nafagen to put a level cap on those encounters which didn't really work out and I doubt they would ever put another level cap into the game. The only alternative is to raise the level of the zone itself.<br><br>Planes were just never meant to be farmed so easily.<br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufelwig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felwig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/01 6:08:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question </span><hr size=1> I really have no problems with a PoH/PoF upgrade, I actually think it'd be a great idea to up it on both the Risk and Reward scales.  Turn it from a boring farm with mediocre rewards to a zone filled with challenging fighting for excellent rewards, and great, you'll hear no complaining from me.<br><br>The thing I see happening is going to be classic Verant overbalancing, though.  I fully expect to see things like Scarelings going from meleeing for 150-160 damage (is that right? It's been a while.) and backstabbing for 400-something to meleeing for 250 and backstabbing for 800 or something silly like that.  With three of them pathing by the zone-in every 15 seconds or so to make sure there are no safe spots, so they can greet you with said backstabs while you're still zoning in.  It's most likely going to change from relatively easy farming to impossibly buggy, linked-aggro weirdness that just winds up ruining one of EQ's major rites of passage (first planar raid), and makes the baseline high-level equipment much harder to get.<br><br>Maybe they'll prove me wrong, but they've been on such a rampage of forcing high-level encounters, I'll be very surprised if any of these tweaks will have any positive effects on the game, let alone make things just more fun. <p>Felwig Figwellen <BR>59 Conjurer <BR>Apex, Luclin server<BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unazlith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazlith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/01 6:38:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cazic and Inny on Drugs</span><hr size=1> Everyone in LoS and Apex should stop posting how easy PoF and PoH are and remember most guilds DON'T have tons of people 55+, with epics and other awesome equipment, and lots of planar raids under their belts.  For many of us out there, these planes still ARE challenging.  As Lorrux mentioned, wipeouts still occur on planar raids.<br><br>I think upgrading the Gods is a great idea, but making the zones more difficult as a whole is a terrible idea.  We'll see what Verant actually does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufelwig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felwig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/01 8:07:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cazic and Inny on Drugs</span><hr size=1> Sorry about that, didn't mean for it to come off as being so elitist.  I think the important thing to remember is that pre-Kunark, the planes were the very definition of a difficult, high-level encounter, with the exception of Vox and Nagafen.  Even on a raid composed entirely of people from outside the most &quot;uber&quot; guilds, they have a much easier time in the planes than they were originally intended to be.  Your average level 50 now is far better-equipped from some of the insane weapon drops in Karnor's and Sebilis.  Things like Jade Maces, Tranquil Staves, Lamentations, Locustlures, and Lupine Daggers are on a completely different level than the high-end weapons of the old world, and are roughly as common as a Ykesha was pre-Kunark.  Throw in the far higher AC (compared to old pre-planar gear)of the Kunark and Velious armor, and your average level 50 tank can give and take significantly more damage than the best-equipped warrior from the old world.  Toss in some 52+ wizards with Lures, and no mob is safe from being burned in down in a hurry, either.<br><br>There are absolutely still wipe-outs on the planes, and they can happen to anyone, no matter how &quot;uber&quot; they think they are.  For me, one of the things about EQ that makes it fun is that no matter where you are, you're never really safe.  Hell, I spaced out while autorunning in Lavastorm the other today while running uninvis'd and blundered into the camp of shadowed men.  They got me down to half a bubble of health left before I managed to gate out.  Talk about a humbling experience, yeesh.<br><br>But that said, I think our concerns are pretty much the same.  Verant *always* balances the game to the highest-level, most aggressive players, and all it takes is one group of the best-equipped level 60's in the game to clear Fear (I'd be surprised if this isn't what prompted the whole retuning of the planes.  It was a group of 8 people level 60ish killing Vox that inspired them to make the level cap), to send Verant off into a fervor of redesign.  And they'll do it in their typical fashion of going to the opposite extreme and making things impossibly difficult.  This hurts everyone, and doesn't apply to just the planes.  Speaking from the perspective of someone who's in Apex, sure we've got a lot of epics, kill Trak, etc., but I'd say we rate pretty low on the uber scale.  We're still working on Veeshan's Peak keys, and there are still tons of places we want to explore and of course, loot we'd love to get to make sure our people are equipped as well as we can outfit them.  There are plenty of guilds out there who clear Veeshan's Peak weekly without batting an eye, then march on in and kill mobs like the Dain, Yelinak, Velketor (although much less so with the new healing aggro changes).  Verant tunes their game to guilds like Fires of Heaven, Afterlife, Da'Kor, and Legacy of Steel, then everyone else suffers.<br><br>Fighting in the Planes is really, really cool.  I remember well my first planes raid ever (to Fear), and I still wear the Cryosilk Amice I got on that trip with pride.  I sincerely hope they don't go overboard with the changes, because it'd ruin one of the major EQ rites of passage.  The planes are the first time many people ever get an opportunity to fight in a large, multi-group situation and experience both the difference in gameplay between one group and five groups, and the general weirdness and fun you can get when you've got 30 people who spend all day camping out in a plane for their armor.<br><br> <p>Felwig Figwellen <BR>59 Conjurer <BR>Apex, Luclin server<BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unazlith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazlith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/01 8:29:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cazic and Inny on Drugs</span><hr size=1> I just find it ironic that the people who say 'Nerfing planes is probably the only way to keep things balance' are the people in the guilds that have been able to farm the planes for several months.  Really what they are saying is that such a nerf is the only way to keep things in balance for the upper 5% of players (if even that much!)<br><br>I think it would be great if they can find a way to buff Cazic and Inno without making the planes too difficult for today's level 46 to 50 players.  In my opinion PoF and PoH can be easier today than they were pre-Kunark because there are tougher challenges. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unazlith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazlith</A> at: 2/28/01 9:16:16 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=624.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showPrevMessage?topicID=624.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showNextMessage?topicID=624.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=624.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/es/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.emailToFriend?topicID=624.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.threadControl?topicID=624.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/es/themes/default/delete